<paragraph id="8BE136BBFFB5EC010390F923FB54F88A" blockId="2.[151,1437,1765,2044]" box="[151,1168,1765,1792]" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">
The five species placed in this subgenus (clade A of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF4B4AFFB5EC0101E6F923FC62F88A" author="Kahnt, B. &amp; Montgomery, G. A. &amp; Murray, E. &amp; Kuhlmann, M. &amp; Pauw, A. &amp; Michez, D. &amp; Paxton, R. J. &amp; Danforth, B. N." box="[737,934,1765,1792]" pageId="2" pageNumber="320" pagination="95 - 105" refId="ref5545" refString="Kahnt, B., Montgomery, G. A., Murray, E., Kuhlmann, M., Pauw, A., Michez, D., Paxton, R. J. &amp; Danforth, B. N. (2017) Playing with extremes: Origins and evolution of exaggerated female forelegs in South African Rediviva bees. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 115, 95 - 105. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2017.07.025" type="journal article" year="2017">
Kahnt 
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC01002AF920FC9AF88A" box="[813,862,1766,1792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
) are listed in table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3446530FFB5EC0003C0F8CFFCC0FE25" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="321" pageId="2" pageNumber="320" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE136BBFFB5EC0103C0F8CFFACCF871" blockId="2.[151,1437,1765,2044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC0103C0F8CFFE86F8AE" bold="true" box="[199,322,1801,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB5EC0102B0F8CCFDDDF8A9" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[439,537,1802,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deriviva">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC0102B0F8CCFDDDF8A9" box="[439,537,1802,1827]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Deriviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a unique combination of lateral lobes of S7 either smooth (not striate) or completely reduced (striate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB5EC0102FEF8E8FD9FF8C2" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1911" box="[505,603,1838,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC0102FEF8E8FD9FF8C2" box="[505,603,1838,1864]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Rediviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21957D2FFB5EC010162F8E8FD5EF8C2" box="[613,666,1838,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="320" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and median lobes either short and hardly longer than their basal width (much broader than long in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB5EC010111F894FDB9F8E6" authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[534,637,1874,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Gigaviva">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC010111F894FDB9F8E6" box="[534,637,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Gigaviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or if longer forming jointly ± a right angle (acute-angled or parallel in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB5EC010390F8B0FF3DF81A" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,249,1910,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC010390F8B0FF3DF81A" box="[151,249,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Rediviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21957D2FFB5EC0103F8F8B0FEF1F81A" box="[255,309,1910,1936]" pageId="2" pageNumber="320" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); median lobes not distinctly apically broadened (
<figureCitation id="13652A3EFFB5EC010058F8B3FC61F805" box="[863,933,1909,1935]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,513,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,453,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rediviva (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♂: a. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view; b. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view; c. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: d. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view; e. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view; f. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889565/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Figs 2</figureCitation>
a–b, d–e) (spatulate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB5EC0107A5F8B0FB3BF81A" authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[1186,1279,1910,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Albiviva">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC0107A5F8B0FB3BF81A" box="[1186,1279,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Albiviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Apical plate of S8 distally notched (
<figureCitation id="13652A3EFFB5EC0102A5F85FFE37F83E" box="[418,499,1945,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,513,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,453,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rediviva (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♂: a. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view; b. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view; c. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: d. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view; e. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view; f. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889565/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
) (strait, deeply cleft, emarginate or semi-circular in other subgenera), except in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB5EC010683F85CFED4F852" authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC010683F85CFED4F852" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">R. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where it is evenly rounded (
<figureCitation id="13652A3EFFB5EC010150F87BFD63F852" box="[599,679,1981,2008]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,513,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,453,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rediviva (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♂: a. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view; b. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view; c. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: d. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view; e. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view; f. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889565/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB5EC01002FF878FC73F852" box="[808,951,1982,2008]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC01002FF878FC73F852" box="[808,951,1982,2008]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Redivivoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species fit this diagnosis and are currently indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB5EC01029CF824FE39F871" box="[411,509,2018,2043]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deriviva">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB5EC01029CF824FE39F871" box="[411,509,2018,2043]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="320">Deriviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
so can only be assigned to a subgenus through the associated female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE136BBFFB4EC0003C0FF5FFCC0FE25" blockId="3.[151,1437,153,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">
Females of three of the five species (Table 1) in this subgenus (
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC000088FF5CFBE3FF39" authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2001" box="[911,1063,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC000088FF5CFBE3FF39" box="[911,1063,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">R. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC000732FF5CFA87FF39" box="[1077,1347,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC000732FF5CFB0FFF39" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[1077,1227,154,179]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermixta">R. intermixta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC0007D1FF5CFA87FF39" box="[1238,1347,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">R. rufipes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) can be identified by a broadened hind tibia and basitarsus with the scopa consisting of densely plumose pubescence for transporting floral oil (
<figureCitation id="13652A3EFFB4EC000290FF27FE20FF76" box="[407,484,225,252]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC00011DFF27FD6DFF71" box="[538,681,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC00011DFF27FD6DFF71" box="[538,681,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">Redivivoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hind tibia not broadened and without plumose pubescence), bidentate mandible (tridentate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC0002CCFEC3FDF6FE95" authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[459,562,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Gigaviva">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC0002CCFEC3FDF6FE95" box="[459,562,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">Gigaviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and inconspicuous yellowish apical tergal hair bands (
<figureCitation id="13652A3EFFB4EC00079BFEC3FB29FEAA" box="[1180,1261,261,288]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
) (distinct white apical hair bands in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC00027BFEEFFE1DFEC9" authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[380,473,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Albiviva">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC00027BFEEFFE1DFEC9" box="[380,473,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">Albiviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in combination with a small shiny scale-like projection on the distal-dorsal angle of the hind basitarsus (
<figureCitation id="13652A3EFFB4EC00027EFE8BFE08FEED" box="[377,460,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC000107FE88FD5DFEED" authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2001" box="[512,665,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC000107FE88FD5DFEED" box="[512,665,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">R. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC0001D6FE88FCFBFEED" box="[721,831,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC0001D6FE88FCFBFEED" box="[721,831,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">R. rufipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this projection is in combination with an apical hairy spine on the front coxa (
<figureCitation id="13652A3EFFB4EC0002AFFEB7FE38FE06" box="[424,508,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">Fig. 3d</figureCitation>
). The remaining two species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC00004CFEB4FC0DFE01" authorityName="Michener" authorityYear="1981" box="[843,969,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colorata">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC00004CFEB4FC0DFE01" box="[843,969,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">R. colorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC000707FEB4FB43FE01" authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="1992" box="[1024,1159,370,395]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saetigera">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC000707FEB4FB43FE01" box="[1024,1159,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">R. saetigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, lack this projection and cannot be distinguished from females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB4EC000167FE53FD06FE25" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1911" box="[608,706,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB4EC000167FE53FD06FE25" box="[608,706,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="321">Rediviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21957D2FFB4EC0001CEFE53FCC0FE25" box="[713,772,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="321" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
