<subSubSection id="C3446530FFB3EC0703C0FF5FFEC6FF5D" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE136BBFFB3EC0703C0FF5FFEC6FF5D" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB3EC0703C0FF5FFE8AFF39" bold="true" box="[199,334,153,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new subgeneric name is an anagram of the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D38FFB3EC07070EFF5FFBAFFF39" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1911" box="[1033,1131,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92AEAA9FFB3EC07070EFF5FFBAFFF39" box="[1033,1131,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Rediviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gender of the name is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3446530FFB3EC0703C0FF26FE5BFE95" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" type="distribution">
